@node intro "Introduction"
@{jcenter}
@{fg highlight}@{b}What is ModePro?@{ub}@{fg text}
@{jleft}
@wordwrap
ModePro is an application or screen specific screen "promoter" for WB 2.1(or WB2.04 and ASL v38) and above.  ModePro also is a simple public screen manager.  You can define public screens that automatically open and close as needed.

ModePro determines which screens to promote via three lists:
@{b}· Screen Names@{ub}  - Lists screens by name that should be promoted.
@{b}· Program Names@{ub} - Lists programs whose screens should be promoted.
@{b}· Screen Modes@{ub}  - Lists screen modes that sould be promoted.
    (see @{"Promotion List Gadgets" link list})

Each list can contain any number of promotion @{b}entry@{ub} names.  When a program attempts to open a screen, ModePro will search the lists in the order above.  If it finds an entry that matches the screen, ModePro will promote the screen using the options the entry specifies.  ModePro allows you to use any AmigaDOS wildcards for the entry names.       

There is also a fourth list, 
@{b}· Public Screens@{ub} - List of public screens ModePro will manage.

This is where ModePro keeps a list of Public Screens, when these public screens are requested by other programs, ModePro will open them, and when the public screen isn't needed anymore, ModePro will close it.  Most of the options available to Promoted screens are available to Public screens.  Also see @{"Creating a Public Screen Entry" link createpubscreens}

ModePro can promote a screen's mode (or Display ID) 4 different ways:
@{b}· Specify the Monitor Type@{ub} - In this case you can change for ex. an NTSC screenmode to PAL.
@{b}· Specify the exact Screen Mode, and optionally Depth and Palette@{ub}
@{b}· Have a ScreenMode requester pop up each time the screen is opened@{ub}
@{b}· ModePro can open a screen that best suits your dimensions (Width, Height, Colors)@{ub}
@{b}· Or ModePro can be told not to promote the screen mode at all.@{ub} - so you can use ModePro's other features.
    (see @{"Promotion Method & Dimension Gadgets" link method})

You can also specify these options for all promotion methods:
@{b}· Autoscroll@{ub}
@{b}· Center@{ub}
@{b}· Interleaved screen bitmaps. (V39+)@{ub}
@{b}· Force screens to be planar. (V39+)@{ub}
    (see @{"Option Gadgets" link options})
@{b}· The WB2+ 3D look for the windows and screen@{ub}
    (see @{"3-D Look Gadgets" link 3dlook})
@{b}· The screens font.@{ub}
    (see @{"Font Gadgets" link fontcont})
@{b}· Make the screen Public.@{ub}
    (see @{"Public Screen Gadgets" link pubcont})
@{b}· Create a screen to front HotKey.@{ub} 
    (see @{"Screen Hot Key Gadgets" link scrhotkey})
@{b}· Shared screen pens. (V39+)@{ub}
    (see @{"Shared Pen Gadgets" link share})
  
ModePro has two global options:
@{b}· NewLook Menus@{ub} - Makes all GadTools menus use the v39 "NewLook", typically black letters on white background, however this can be overriden using the 3D pen options.
@{b}· Center Unknown Screens@{ub} - all non-promoted screens can be centered.
    (see @{"Menus" link menus})   
@endnode


